<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>	<item><state>ME</state><who>TT'rs</who><category><shortname>community-environment</shortname><id>4</id><name>community/environment</name></category><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : medium"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cheers all, and Welcome!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Meet or talk with other people who are interested in helping their community utilize the Transition Town concept to effectively and positively address the issues of reduced energy, economic crisis and changing climate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;While this meetup will provide information on awareness raising and sanctioned training events happening in Maine, anyone from any community is welcome! The Transition Town concept is unusual in that it:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;*  is based on permaculture principles&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;*  is bottom up and adaptive, rather than top down and prescriptive.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;*  recognizes our need to envision a positive future.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;* ena&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : medium"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;bles us to act on that vision by unleashing our collective genius.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;There are now 134 official Transition Initiatives in the US and more than 400 globally&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;More information on the Transition movement in the US can be found at &lt;strong&gt;www.transitionus.org&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;

